title: Portrait of a Woman

thumbnail.alt_text: A work made of oil on panel.

exhibition_history:
Art Institute of Chicago, A Century of Progress, June 1 - November 1, 1934, no. 97.

Art Institute of Chicago, Rembrandt after Three Hundred Years:  An Exhibition of Rembrandt and His Followers, October 25 - December 7, 1969, traveled to the Minneapolis Institute of Arts, December 22, 1969 - February 1, 1970, and the Detroit Institute of Arts, February 24 - April 5, 1970, no. 84.
provenance_text: Gustave Rothan, Paris, by 1873 [Mantz 1873]; sold Paris, Galerie Georges Petit, May 29-31, 1890, no. 71.  Charles Hutchinson, Chicago (died 1924), by 1894; probably acquired by him with its pendant, 1925.716, at the Rothan sale; bequeathed to the Art Institute, 1925.
